to play and force the win.} ({Necessary was} 28... Qc8 {.}) 29. Bc6 $1 {ANSWER:
Removal of the guard. --- Outwardly the bishop shrouds himself in godliness,
while inwardly he calculates and manipulates, always toward his self-interests.
} Red8 ({Also,} 29... Rf8 {allows White exactly the same idea after} 30. Rxe6
$1 fxe6 31. Qxe6+ Kg7 32. Qe7+ {winning.}) 30. Rxe6 $1 {That which was once
